<pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMMM8DGZuik02gI0Su9gn3ftAolJgjF7XlgANvj=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</pics><gmapID>0x8091f7a7281a94af:0x44210fb9e283a602< /gmapID><Resp>None</Resp><Time>1614221837913</Time>< text>
This place has the best shrimp burritos! I've had them 3 times now (excessive, I know but worth every calorie) and they are perfect every time! They are cheesy, just perfect amount of everything, except this last time it was usually skimpy on the shrimp. My boyfriend has tried the nacho fries and nachos and has felt disappointment both times,  the cheese doesn't melt, his nacho fries didn't have much al pastor and the cheese wasn't melted on either. They have great tacos, too. Their red salsa is on point! Flavorful and spicy! While my boyfriend is not the greatest fan (he's pickier than I), I love this place, good food, great service, always fast.</text>

< Review>
Has everything you would hope to find in regards to it being a liquor store, and also has some things available that you wouldn't expect, like extension cords and cigars that are actually a good selection for a local liquor spot. Also has some things like BANG energy drinks for a great buy of 2 for $4. And if you enjoy some pistachios or peanuts with your favorite drinks they have some great little zip lock bags with some inside, so just stop by if your a local to silver lakes, it's well worth cutting out the drive outside of here to get very similarly priced things that are offered here without the drive.</Review>

<Resp>None<//Resp><text>COOLEST Panera Bread store I've ever experienced! I walked in and immediately fell in love with the space. It's got a warm industrial-modern feel with high ceilings, rustic wood tables and exposed brick walls. I'm so excited that we now have a store in Beverly Hills. The Hot Turkey Panini w/ a cup of Tomato soup is my all-time favorite. Today I tried the LENTIL QUINOA BOWL WITH CHICKEN and it was DELICIOUS. It had fresh kale and spinach, quinoa and lentils, antibiotic-free chicken, all in a flavorful soy-miso broth. You have to try it!!!

Overall: There is such a unique vibe in the store that I've never experienced at any other Panera. Plus, the food is incredible. There's free wifi, staff is attentive yet knows when to leave you alone. I see it as a great working space to go/hang out on the computer writing and relaxing.

Loved it. Proud to be the first to share this awesome cafe with everyone on Yelp. So glad I finally have a Panera in Beverly Hills, Beverly blvd is now complete!</text>< gmap_id>

On top of it they state it takes 4-6 WEEKS just to enter someone in the "system" and it takes at least 6 weeks to receive a paycheck once they've fully processed ones paperwork, which would be ILLEGAL FOR ANY COMPANY IN CA to do to people. The director and people who drag their feet while working there should be ashamed of themselves.</Text>

<text>I picked up my Sprinter this past week.  I interacted with five dealerships over the summer before deciding on Temecula MB, and not one of those other dealers compared with Lauren Rose's responsiveness, knowledge of the Sprinter, or ease in building a personal connection. Nolan responded immediately after I submitted an inquiry and provided several build sheets with options I was considering. < review>
My wife and I were next door at the Audi dealership. We went so she could try a few options there before picking her next car. She had never picked her own car before, I always just went and got her one when the previous lease was ending. At any rate the plan was to have her test the Q8 which she was really attracted to but scared of because it‚Äôs much larger than her current Land Rover Discovery Sport. And then try a crossover or midsized model, the Q3 or Q5 and maybe even try a sedan or one of their wagons before making a decision. Just to give herself the opportunity to try out the options. Long story short, the gentleman at the Audi dealership took one look at us ( to be fair I was just wearing jeans and an old band tee, she had on a very casual outfit and our daughter was taking a nap so as he approached us while we got out of my truck we probably appeared a bit disheveled, transferring her from the car seat to the stroller )and talked her out driving the Q8 and had her test a base model Q7. I stayed with our daughter in the show room. After a short drive she was very unimpressed with the trim level having driven the Q8 prestige in Carlsbad a few weeks prior. I asked if he could pull out a few more options for her to test while our daughter was still asleep because once she woke the chance of us having a chance to rationally discuss the options would diminish and the idea of making a decision would likely disappear all together. He said, ‚ÄúThey‚Äôre all Audi. They all drive the same. Why don‚Äôt you guys take a look around the show room   And decide what you want‚Äù . I asked if he meant to tell me the base model q3 offered the same driving experience as say an sq5 or the Q8 prestige trim level and so we went next door to Fletcher Jones‚Äôs Mercedes of Temecula. In all honesty we‚Äôd never really considered a Benz for our family. My wife never saw one up to that day that compelled her visually and all of my friends and colleagues seem to have either  upper tier e class or s class as their daily drivers and so The brand always just seemed so average to me.
And then she saw it. I won‚Äôt say which model but I will tell you this, she saw the AMG version and fell immediately in love. We just went to look not buy but I knew the second I saw her response to that vehicle that we‚Äôd be leaving with it: however, I had no idea how painless, even enjoyable the team at fletcher jones was going to make the leasing process. Michael was our sales rep and he went above and beyond and above again to make certain we had excellent service, got the best possible options available, (the first one she saw it turned out didnt have the color interior she wanted,  or heated or cooled seats which she wanted and in short order Michael rounded up one that had all the options we wanted and a few we hadn‚Äôt really considered yet, but were happy have included) and worked quite a surprisingly good deal out to keep our monthly down, maintain zero out of pocket and roll in the maintenance and the lease protection program, all under the initial figure I told him I was willing accept as a monthly payment. Not only that but we were in and out of there in under 2 hours. Let that sink in. Under 2 hours to purchase/ lease a vehicle. I‚Äôve had it take longer to upgrade my phone. I know what you‚Äôre saying, no way, this is too good to be true, there‚Äôs no way I‚Äôd have the same experience there. Listen, give these guys a shot at your business, you won‚Äôt be disappointed. < review>
MB Temecula just opened.  When I went in even though it was a Tuesday afternoon, they seemed busy, but everyone greeted me with a smile.  I was introduced to a salesman, Bob Crabtree, who while a car (and MB) veteran, had only been on the job at MB Temecula for a few days.

Bob was amazingly helpful, even though I had no intention of purchasing a vehicle that day.  He went above and beyond what I would have expected.  By the time we were done chatting, he actually gave me a deal better than even I was asking for and I ended up purchasing the vehicle.

The entire team at MB Temecula is there, from the GM Antony to the Sales Manager Vince, they all were amazingly helpful.  Temecula is all about community and treating people right.  The business that succeed here get that.  MB Temecula is off to a great start in that fashion.  They understand us and are not a typical auto mall type operation.  They are really here to succeed and want to be a part of our neighborhood.

I have purchased several cars in my life, and this was by far the most painless, and dare I say, enjoyable experience.  I look forward to poking my head in weekly when I'm getting my free car wash just to see the goings on.

Thank you very much MB Temecula team!< /review>

I had a very bad experience with this place.  I emailed and spoke with several dealerships to get a feel for car discounts offered.  In the Temacula dealership, I spoke with Nolen. Mercedes-Benz Fletcher Jones of Temecula:
Will sell you a NEW vehicle that has been in a accident or has had prior Damage. If you purchased a vehicle here Please have it inspected.
I purchased a new Sprinter Van about 10 months ago to transport my 85 year old mother who has Parkinson and is severely handicapped so i can get her in and out of a high top van with ease.
It was getting late in the evening so it was already getting dark. I Picked out a nice midnight blue van not even thinking that there would be any damage. While talking to the sales manager she disclosed to me that this vehicle was there oldest vehicle and it has been sitting on there lot for almost a year. I asked her why that was and she really did not have a valid answer now I know why . its because of all the damage.
After signing all the paperwork and they brought it into there bay I noticed some scratches and imperfections. Not doing a thurl inspection I had no idea the extent of the damages on the passenger side where it had been repainted. I was assured by the manager that she would file a claim to get everything fixed and put everything in writing in a due bill. So I went ahead and took the vehicle home. when i awoke the next morning i noticed a lot more damage in the sunlight. I called immediately and was told to speak with Steve Usary he is the service manager he made me an appointment and told me i would get a loaner car while they were going to get all repairs completed. I took the day off of work and drove the 3 hours it takes for me to get there. When i brought the vehicle in they brought there painter out to inspect the vehicle and my partner overheard him tell Steve that the vehicle was too big for there paint booth and had too much damage to repair at there facility . So then Steve told  me that it was beyond his approval and that he would have to file a claim with Mercedes. So I asked him can i just exchange the vehicle out for another one since i only had it for a few days and he told me no it will have to be  traded in. So i said ok im willing to trade it in then.
and he said. These are his exact words.
" WELL IF YOU TRADE IT IN I CANT GIVE YOU MUCH FOR IT BECAUSE OF THE EXTENT OF THE DAMAGE "    WOW can you believe that.
I was floored. then he went on to ask me if i liked how the vehicle ran and how it drove. i told him it ran great. and his response was. " WHY ARE YOU COMPLAINING YOU HAVE A NICE VEHICE. Unbelievable the audacity of this man. so in other words he saying if the vehicle runs and drives good it does not matter what it looks like. I would expect to find this guy in a 2bit used car lot NOT a new Mercedes store.  He then assured me that he would be in contact with me after he put in a claim with Mercedes.  I took it into a few body shops and got a couple estimates it was 4000 to do the passenger side and over 9000 to do the whole vehicle because there are scratch's and blemish's everywhere.
10 months later and i have still not heard anything. So i contacted Mercedes they told me it was out of there hands that it is up to Fletcher Jones to take care of it.
